---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import CTA from "../../components/CTA.astro";
import RuntimeDiagram from "../../components/RuntimeDiagram.astro";
---

<Layout title="GitHub Agent Behavior Review Prototype">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="shell page-hero__body">
      <div class="page-hero__text">
        <p class="eyebrow">Possible POC</p>
        <h1 class="headline-xl">GitHub agent behavior review and control prototype.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          GitHub is a useful prototype surface because coding agents are visible,
          useful, and risky. The POC tests whether Semantiv can turn messy behavior
          into meaning, evidence, authority, coordination, control, and record.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="page-hero__meta">
        <p>Not a branch-protection wrapper. A reviewable slice of agent behavior and control.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--paper">
    <div class="shell section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">01 Demo flow</div>
      <div class="section-body split">
        <div>
          <h2 class="headline-lg">An agent wants to modify code in a production repository.</h2>
          <p class="lede">
            The important question is not only whether the path is allowed. It is
            what the change means, what evidence supports it, who needs to review it,
            and what action should be allowed, blocked, escalated, or recorded.
          </p>
        </div>
        <RuntimeDiagram
          title="demo flow"
          steps={["agent proposes repository work", "trace, diff, tests, and approvals reviewed", "operational meaning assigned", "evidence and authority checked", "control recommendation produced", "decision record stored"]}
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="shell section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">02 MVP actions</div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="grid-list">
          <article class="grid-item">
            <span class="grid-item__label">ReadRepo</span>
            <h3>Agent reads files or metadata</h3>
            <p>Which context did the agent rely on?</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-item">
            <span class="grid-item__label">ProposeChange</span>
            <h3>Agent produces a diff or patch</h3>
            <p>What system behavior is affected?</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-item">
            <span class="grid-item__label">OpenPullRequest</span>
            <h3>Agent creates a branch and PR</h3>
            <p>What work is being submitted for review?</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-item">
            <span class="grid-item__label">RequestReview</span>
            <h3>Agent asks for human review</h3>
            <p>What authority is being requested?</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-item">
            <span class="grid-item__label">AttemptMerge</span>
            <h3>Agent tries to merge</h3>
            <p>Is the system allowed to accept this work now?</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-item">
            <span class="grid-item__label">ModifyProtectedPath</span>
            <h3>Agent changes protected files</h3>
            <p>What business or security obligation may be affected?</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--dark">
    <div class="shell section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">03 Core types</div>
      <div class="section-body split">
        <div>
          <h2 class="headline-lg">A small console, not a general platform.</h2>
          <p class="lede">
            The prototype should show behavior trace, operational meaning, evidence
            packet, missing evidence, authority requirement, control recommendation,
            and decision record.
          </p>
        </div>
        <pre class="code-block">BehaviorTrace
ActionMeaning
EvidencePacket
AuthorityContext
ControlRecommendation
DecisionRecord</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--paper">
    <div class="shell section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">04 Proves</div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <h2 class="headline-lg">What this POC proves.</h2>
        <ul class="rule-list">
          <li><code>01</code><span>Semantiv can review real agent behavior, not only static policy.</span></li>
          <li><code>02</code><span>Operational meaning can be extracted from traces and artifacts.</span></li>
          <li><code>03</code><span>Evidence gaps can be made explicit.</span></li>
          <li><code>04</code><span>Coordination and authority can be modeled.</span></li>
          <li><code>05</code><span>A decision record can explain why work should proceed or stop.</span></li>
          <li><code>06</code><span>The same method can apply beyond GitHub.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA
    title="Use GitHub as a concrete slice, not as the company."
    copy="The POC succeeds when it helps a team understand what an agent changed, what that change means, what evidence exists, and what control should apply."
    secondaryHref="/cases/coding-agents"
    secondaryLabel="View coding-agent case"
  />
</Layout>
